<manpage>
    <sample url="sdk\eztypes\EzWCharBuf\EzWCharBuf_">EzWCharBuf_</sample>
    <volume> Common Data Structure </volume>
    <function>template&lt;UINT SIZE&gt; EzWCharBuf_::EzWCharBuf_</function>

    <description>
        <para> Constructor of an EzWCharBuf object, constructs an EzWCharBuf object and allocates memory blocks for it. </para>
    </description>

    <syntax_nopara>
        <apiname>EzWCharBuf_</apiname>
        <NoArguments/>
    </syntax_nopara>

    <remarks>
        <para> EzWCharBuf_ is a template class, an EzWCharBuf subclass. The template parameter <i>SIZE</i> specifies number of Unicode characters in the buffer.</para>
        <para> This function can allocate memory in stack (if declared the EzWCharBuf object as local variable) or in data segment (if declared the EzByteBuf object as static or global variable).</para>
        <para>Note: Cannot create EzWCharBuf object with this function while in the scope of the function started with extern "C".</para>
    </remarks>

